It wasn't easy as both fighters showed their ruthlessness and why they are called champions. Ultimately, Unnati let out a blitzkrieg and ripped apart Hetal to win.
Komal is fighting like a champion as she defeated Aishwarya perfectly. She's slowly got the tactical mind of being in a title hunt.

However, one powerful stray kick from Rushika betrayed Sayali. The power behind that kick was enough to confuse a poor Sayali who was then beaten to crap by a rampant Rushika. Rushika saved the best for last as she withdrew just before Sayali would be knocked out only to place a steely kick that knocked out the former champion to the relegation zone.

Kinjal showed all the finer nuances of a professionally trained MMA fighter competing at the highest level as she dispatched off Kripa Jalan with barely any impactful strikes hitting herself. Kinjal was exceptional as she struck with inch-perfect accuracy before taking Kripa down with a perfect triangle choke and blasting away her face with incredibly strong punches. A majestic win!
A quick in and out affair as Unnati barely gave Aishwarya chance to strike and wrapped her in a cold rear naked choke hold to finish the fight. Confidence.

10 seconds knockout. Sayali took 10 seconds to weight her opponent before feigning a thunderous tornado trick kick to shock Komal. Komal never got a chance to use her skills or strike as she was cleanly knocked out by the power of that kick. Sayali followed it up with brutal punches to all but wrap up the win.

Mahima was left speechless as Rushika finished her with lethal Taekwondo kicks. Rushika was excellent at finding gaps and applying just the right pressure to derail Mahima. The impact of the kicks was so strong that Mahima was already dizzying by the second kick. The rest were just additions to knock Mahima out. A kicky stunning affair with a toned body for Rushika.

Kinjal was doing just great as she inflicted some serious strikes on Venessa without a reply. That was until Venessa attempted her first few strikes and a nasty hook to the side completely derailed Kinjal. Kinjal was unable to get past the pain and Venessa used her distraction to full use as she brought her down and pounded her to a win.
Sayali had no chance as Unnati wrecked havoc with Hetal present in the stands.

Komal was clearly the better fighter and outclassing Mahima until the final third of the fight. Mahima was left annoyed and frustrated by how Komal was able to fight better than her. So, Mahima opted for a random vicious street-style brawling that surprised both the referee and Komal. Komal still managed to have the upper hand until the last five minutes where Mahima called back her supreme skillsets to place Komal in a rear-naked choke to end the fight.

Venessa was dominant in the first half where she nearly decimated Rushika without giving her a space to breathe. When Rushika finally composed herself, she took little time to take back the dominance and then using her strong kicks, destroyed Venessa. Both used their respective skills to the fullest.
Unnati ripped apart Mahima ferociously. Mahima's leg was the first to be shattered before the former unleashed hell.

Surreal power in the kick as Rushika blanks out Komal with a powerful kick to the face after Komal manages to trap her kick. Rushika was constantly peppering Komal with nasty powerful kicks before that thunderbolt. She finished off the fight with some good old punches to the face.
Three powerful kicks were the highlight of the fight that completely derailed Venessa.
Brutal but perfect kicks by Kripa.
Vicious by Sayali, back in form.
Furious win. Hetal doesn't wait for a post-fight conference as she storms out of the arena and sits in her car after losing the top spot and Invicta Cup in Australia.

Supriya was listless as Hinal ran circles around her and finally deservingly won the fight.
Amruta was phenomenal as she matched Isha's energy and wrapped up the fight with a majestic triangle choke while resisting Isha's move to lift her up while in triangle choke. Ferocious!

Every kick and punch was devastating as she bullied Vinaya to win this fight. Championesque win for Anmol!
Bullish win. Zero strikes by Anika.

Ishita vent out all her fury on Ashwini.

Diana was excellent and should have been the winner. It was an agonisingly long fight as equals. Both fighters were persistent although it looked like Diana needed this more than Kanchan. Eventually, Kanchan managed to trap Diana in a rear naked chokehold.

Aashna was majestic. Kanchan never bad a chance to strike Aashna. Aashna was supremely professional and insanely calm as she thwarted every Kanchan strike and struck back stronger. Eventually that perfect chokehold was enough to bring a historic win. A win that reminds of her glory days when she chased the title.
Kanchan rips apart Ananya's face in a vicious war that saw them engage in an intense street style battle for win.

Vicious battle as the two fighters looked to be on a personal agenda to finish each other off. Fight moved from a professional environment to a poor impression of a street brawl. Ananya finished it off with a flurry of punches.

Supreme skills by Vidhi to dodge Sachi's incoming strike, move behind her, shove her to the right distance before unleashing a lethal kick to the jaw that knocked Sachi out. However, Kanchan flipped the tables suddenly and put on such a dominating force that Shraddha couldn't handle. Eventually, Kanchan let out her anger and brutally disfigured Shraddha to confirm her second place finish this season while breaking her arm.

Kriti reserved one of her best performances for the last as she dominated and beat Aashna down to mincemeat. This was a flawless top-notch performance of highest professional standards that got Krishi to the top ten in IFC rankings earlier in the season. They was just about perfect power behind each strike, perfect accuracy, and lethal skills at display with merciless brutality as she won against an in-form Aashna Jogani.

The most brutal fight was reserved for the last fight of Division 3. Diana absolutely battered the shit out of Mridula in the first half. Mridula had no answer whatsoever as she Diana rained punches, kicks and holds. However, Diana was this close to finishing off the fight when Mridula made an epic comeback. Having stronger legs than her Australian counterpart and more agility, Mridula ripped apart the challenge to pieces and brutally destroyed Diana by breaking her arm and her face to win the fight.
